jaco.swing.autocomplete

Class DefaultCompletionProvider<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jaco.swing.autocomplete.DefaultCompletionProvider<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the data type of completions
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompletionProvider<E>

    public class DefaultCompletionProvider<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements CompletionProvider<E>
    The default completion provider whose data source is backed by a given collection. This implementation keeps its own copy of data list and automatically sorts the list for faster lookup of entries.

    • Method Detail

      • getCompletions

        public java.util.Collection<E> getCompletions(TokenChangedEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: CompletionProvider
        Returns a collection of completions to suggest to the user based on the TokenChangedEvent.

        An implementation of this method must filter the data based on the provided term of the TokenChangedEvent. TokenChangedEvent.getLimitHint() provides a hint about the maximum number of values to display in the Autocomplete list. In practice, the hint should be used by the implementation to limit the number of results to fetch from the data source.

        Specified by:
        getCompletions in interface CompletionProvider<E>
        Parameters:
        event - the event invoking suggestions
        Returns:
        a collection of data values to suggest to the user
